#. Import macro tooltip
msgid ""
"Import a .json macro file.\n"
"Format: {name, actions: [{type, key/ms/text, delay_after_ms}], repeat_mode}\n"
"Action types: key_down, key_up, delay, text, mouse_click, scroll"
msgstr ""
"Import a .json macro file.\n"
"Format: {name, actions: [{type, key/ms/text, delay_after_ms}], repeat_mode}\n"
"Action types: key_down, key_up, delay, text, mouse_click, scroll"

#. Empty macros state description
msgid ""
"Create your first macro to automate key sequences,\n"
"mouse actions, and more."
msgstr ""
"Create your first macro to automate key sequences,\n"
"mouse actions, and more."

#. Delete macro confirmation
msgid ""
"Are you sure you want to delete \"%s\"?\n"
"This cannot be undone."
msgstr ""
"Are you sure you want to delete \"%s\"?\n"
"This cannot be undone."

#. Key capture dialog body
msgid ""
"Press the key you want to add to the macro.\n"
"Press Escape to cancel."
msgstr ""
"Press the key you want to add to the macro.\n"
"Press Escape to cancel."

#. Gaming mode info card
msgid ""
"Gaming mode optimizes your mouse for gaming by switching to a dedicated "
"DPI profile and optionally suppressing the radial menu overlay to prevent "
"accidental activation.\n"
"\n"
"DPI profiles let you quickly switch between precision (low DPI), normal "
"(medium DPI), and fast (high DPI) sensitivities. Macros allow you to "
"record and replay complex input sequences."
msgstr ""
"Gaming mode optimizes your mouse for gaming by switching to a dedicated "
"DPI profile and optionally suppressing the radial menu overlay to prevent "
"accidental activation.\n"
"\n"
"DPI profiles let you quickly switch between precision (low DPI), normal "
"(medium DPI), and fast (high DPI) sensitivities. Macros allow you to "
"record and replay complex input sequences."

#. Timeline empty state
msgid ""
"No actions yet.\n"
"Use the palette below or Record to add actions."
msgstr ""
"No actions yet.\n"
"Use the palette below or Record to add actions."

